'''Abaseen Yousafzai''' ({{lang-ur|اباسين يوسفزي}}) ({{lang-ps|اباسین یوسفزی}}) is a [[Pashtuns|Pashtun]] poet from [[Pakistan]]. He is president of the Pashto Academy of the [[University of Peshawar]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/109441-Abaseen-Yousafzais-poetry-book-launched|title=Abaseen Yousafzai’s poetry book launched|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=2017-01-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/1076674/pashto-poet-abaseen-yousafzai-launches-third-poetry-collection/|title=Pashto poet Abaseen Yousafzai launches third poetry collection - The Express Tribune|date=2016-04-01|newspaper=The Express Tribune|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/yourlanguage/pashto/en/content/interview-abaseen-yousafzai|title=An Interview with ABASEEN YOUSAFZAI|newspaper=SBS Your Language|language=en|access-date=2017-01-28}}</ref> Yousafzai has had his poetry published across the [[Durand Line]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1252383|title=Abaseen Yousafzai praised for his lively and purposeful poetry|date=2016-04-16|newspaper=DAWN.COM|language=en|access-date=2017-01-28}}</ref> Abaseen Yousafzai joined the [[Islamia College Peshawar]] as a lecturer of [[Pashto]] in 1993.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/165983-Pashto-poet-defends-PhD-thesis|title=Pashto poet defends PhD thesis|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=2017-01-29}}</ref>

==Works==
Yousafzai has written three poetry collections: ''Ghurzanguna'' (1994),  ''Alwat'' (2005), and ''Maraam '' (2016). ''Ghurzanguna'' ran to ten editions and ''Alwat'' to five editions. Yousafzai was given a book launch ceremony from the [[Abasin Arts Council]] for ''Alwat''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/109441-Abaseen-Yousafzais-poetry-book-launched|title=Abaseen Yousafzai’s poetry book launched|last=Mahmood|first=Nisar|date=1 April 2016|publisher=The News International|accessdate=30 January 2017}}</ref> His book, ''Da Pakhtunkhwa Bani'', is a biography of Malek Ahmad Baba, who founded the State of Pakhtunkhwa in 1520.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailytimes.com.pk/khyber-pakhtunkhwa/26-Jul-16/book-about-the-founder-of-kp-published|title=Book about the founder of KP published|last=Yusufzai|first=Arshad|date=26 July 2016|work=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|accessdate=30 January 2017}}</ref> Yousafzai conducted research on the concept of nationalism in Pashto poetry. The title of the thesis was "Concept of nationality in the poetry of Hamza Shinwari".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/165983-Pashto-poet-defends-PhD-thesis|title=Pashto poet defends PhD thesis|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=2017-01-29}}</ref>

==Criticism of Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf Party==

Abaseen criticized the policy of [[Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf]] for inciting youth to resort to violence.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://nation.com.pk/islamabad/24-Aug-2014/pti-flayed-for-instigating-pashtun-youth-to-violence|title=PTI flayed for instigating Pashtun youth to violence|newspaper=The Nation|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-29}}</ref>

